The paper proposes a framework for learning from examples that are described by multiple instances and associated with multiple class labels. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR), where objects can have multiple semantic meanings. The proposed algorithms are based on boosting and SVM, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
